Will Allen and his business partner Susan Daub accused of reaping more than $31 million in a Ponzi scheme that promised high returns to investors from funding loans to pro athletes . 
  Securities and Exchange Commission announced charges against Allen and Daub and their Capital Financial Partners investment firms . 
  Allen was a cornerback in the NFL from 2001 to 2012 . 
  SEC alleges pair paid about $20 million to investors but received only $13 million in loan repayments from athletes . 
 